            "control_name": "select + option_group",
            "returns_label": "Pattern \u00b7 CSS value",
            "description": "<p><strong>This is how you get a theme-color dropdown in Fluid.</strong> There's no dedicated 'theme_color' control \u2014 you compose one: a <code>select</code> in your section schema pointed at an <code>option_group</code> defined in <code>config/settings_schema.json</code>.</p>",
            "preview_type": "select",
            "preview_label": "Background Color",
            "preview_value": "Primary",
            "schema_label": "1. Section schema \u2014 the select",
            "schema_snippet": "{ \"type\": \"select\", \"id\": \"background_color\",\n  \"label\": \"Background Color\",\n  \"options\": \"background_colors\",\n  \"default\": \"transparent\" }",
            "schema_snippet_2_label": "2. config/settings_schema.json \u2014 the option_group",
            "schema_snippet_2": "{\n  \"type\": \"color_background\",\n  \"id\": \"color_primary\",\n  \"label\": \"Primary Color\",\n  \"default\": \"#023026\",\n  \"option_group\": {\n    \"id\": \"background_colors\",\n    \"label\": \"Primary\",\n    \"value\": \"var(--clr-primary)\"\n  }\n}",
            "liquid_snippet": "background-color: &#123;&#123; section.settings.background_color | default: 'transparent' &#125;&#125;;",
            "tip_label": "Critical bug to avoid",
            "tip_kind": "warning",
            "tip": "<p>Never wrap the value as <code>var(--clr-&#123;&#123; '&#123;&#123;' &#125;&#125;\u2026&#123;&#123; '&#125;&#125;' &#125;&#125;)</code>. When the setting is empty that renders <code>var(--clr-)</code> \u2014 invalid CSS that silently breaks the entire rule block. The <code>option_group</code>'s <code>value</code> already returns a CSS value (e.g. <code>var(--clr-primary)</code>, <code>transparent</code>).</p>"
          }
        },
