        {
          "type": "schema_entry",
          "settings": {
            "category": "patterns",
            "anchor_id": "pattern-divider-block",
            "is_featured": true,
            "control_name": "Divider Block (Cards / Steps)",
            "returns_label": "Empty block \u00b7 stateful walk in section liquid",
            "description": "<p>Group repeating sub-blocks (image + heading + text + button \u2026) into <strong>cards</strong> by walking blocks statelessly. An empty <code>divider</code> block opens a new card; subsequent canonical blocks render inside until the next divider closes/reopens. Used by <code>feature_grid</code>, <code>testimonial_grid</code>, <code>process_steps</code>.</p>",
            "preview_type": "custom",
            "preview_custom_html": "<div class=\"sr-collapsible\">Pattern</div><div class=\"sr-field-label\" style=\"padding:8px;color:#94a3b8;\">See snippets below</div>",
            "schema_label": "Schema",
            "schema_snippet": "&#123;\n  \"blocks\": [\n    &#123; \"type\": \"step\", \"name\": \"+ New Step\", \"settings\": [\n      &#123; \"type\": \"paragraph\", \"content\": \"Divider block. Add image / heading / text blocks AFTER this.\" &#125;\n    ] &#125;,\n    &#123; \"type\": \"image\",   \"name\": \"Image\",   \"settings\": [ /* canonical image */ ] &#125;,\n    &#123; \"type\": \"heading\", \"name\": \"Heading\", \"settings\": [\n      &#123; \"type\": \"richtext\", \"id\": \"text\", \"label\": \"Title\" &#125;\n    ] &#125;,\n    &#123; \"type\": \"text\", \"name\": \"Text\", \"settings\": [\n      &#123; \"type\": \"richtext\", \"id\": \"text\", \"label\": \"Text\" &#125;\n    ] &#125;\n  ]\n&#125;",
            "liquid_label": "Liquid",
            "liquid_snippet": "&#123;%- assign in_step = false -%&#125;\n&#123;% for block in section.blocks %&#125;\n  &#123;% case block.type %&#125;\n    &#123;% when 'step' %&#125;\n      &#123;% if in_step %&#125;</div>&#123;% endif %&#125;\n      <div class=\"step-card\" &#123;&#123; block.fluid_attributes &#125;&#125;>\n      &#123;% assign in_step = true %&#125;\n    &#123;% when 'image' %&#125;\n      &#123;% if in_step %&#125;&#123;% comment %&#125;render canonical image&#123;% endcomment %&#125;&#123;% endif %&#125;\n    &#123;% when 'heading' %&#125;\n      &#123;% if in_step %&#125;<h3 &#123;&#123; block.fluid_attributes &#125;&#125;>&#123;&#123; block.settings.text &#125;&#125;</h3>&#123;% endif %&#125;\n    &#123;% when 'text' %&#125;\n      &#123;% if in_step %&#125;<div class=\"rte\" &#123;&#123; block.fluid_attributes &#125;&#125;>&#123;&#123; block.settings.text &#125;&#125;</div>&#123;% endif %&#125;\n  &#123;% endcase %&#125;\n&#123;% endfor %&#125;\n&#123;% if in_step %&#125;</div>&#123;% endif %&#125;",
            "tip_label": "Why a divider block instead of nested blocks",
            "tip_kind": "tip",
            "tip": "<p>Fluid doesn't support true block nesting. The divider pattern emulates it by walking the flat block list in order. <strong>Editors learn the rule once</strong>: \"+ New Step\" opens a card, blocks after it render inside until the next \"+ New Step\". Cards stay reorderable as a unit by moving the divider.</p>"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "schema_entry",
          "settings": {
            "category": "patterns",
            "anchor_id": "pattern-theme-fonts",
            "is_featured": true,
            "control_name": "Theme-Driven Fonts",
            "returns_label": "select + options: \"font_families\"",
            "description": "<p>Never use <code>font_picker</code> in section/block settings \u2014 it's disconnected from the theme and lets editors pick any font. Always use a <code>select</code> with <code>options: \"font_families\"</code>. Pulls from the 5-font theme palette: Body / Heading / Accent / Italic / Handwriting.</p>",
            "preview_type": "custom",
            "preview_custom_html": "<div class=\"sr-collapsible\">Pattern</div><div class=\"sr-field-label\" style=\"padding:8px;color:#94a3b8;\">See snippets below</div>",
            "schema_label": "Schema",
            "schema_snippet": "&#123; \"type\": \"select\", \"id\": \"font_family\", \"label\": \"Font Family\",\n  \"options\": \"font_families\",\n  \"default\": \"var(--ff-body)\" &#125;",
            "liquid_label": "Liquid",
            "liquid_snippet": "&#123;% if block.settings.font_family != blank %&#125;\n  font-family: &#123;&#123; block.settings.font_family &#125;&#125;;\n&#123;% endif %&#125;\n\n&#123;# Value is already a CSS var like var(--ff-italic). #&#125;\n&#123;# DO NOT pipe through | font_family \u2014 that's for raw strings only. #&#125;",
            "tip_label": "Theme exposes 5 fonts via option_group",
            "tip_kind": "tip",
            "tip": "<p>For the dropdown to populate, <code>config/settings_schema.json</code> must declare each font with <code>option_group: { id: \"font_families\", label: \"Body\", value: \"var(--ff-body)\" }</code>. Without that metadata, the dropdown shows empty.</p>"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "schema_entry",
          "settings": {
            "category": "patterns",
            "anchor_id": "pattern-split-border",
            "is_featured": true,
            "control_name": "Split Border (width + color)",
            "returns_label": "range + select \u00b7 never native border type",
            "description": "<p>Fluid's native <code>border</code> control uses a <em>hex color picker</em> internally \u2014 disconnected from the theme. Always split into two controls: a <code>range</code> for width, a <code>select + background_colors</code> for color. Same applies to nested borders (Container, items, cards).</p>",
            "preview_type": "custom",
            "preview_custom_html": "<div class=\"sr-collapsible\">Pattern</div><div class=\"sr-field-label\" style=\"padding:8px;color:#94a3b8;\">See snippets below</div>",
            "schema_label": "Schema",
            "schema_snippet": "&#123; \"type\": \"range\",  \"id\": \"border_width\", \"label\": \"Border Width\",\n  \"min\": 0, \"max\": 10, \"step\": 1, \"default\": 0, \"unit\": \"px\" &#125;,\n&#123; \"type\": \"select\", \"id\": \"border_color\", \"label\": \"Border Color\",\n  \"options\": \"background_colors\", \"default\": \"var(--clr-primary)\" &#125;",
            "liquid_label": "Liquid",
            "liquid_snippet": "&#123;% if section.settings.border_width > 0 %&#125;\n  border: &#123;&#123; section.settings.border_width &#125;&#125;px solid &#123;&#123; section.settings.border_color &#125;&#125;;\n&#123;% endif %&#125;"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "schema_entry",
          "settings": {
            "category": "patterns",
            "anchor_id": "pattern-canonical-block-primacy",
            "is_featured": true,
            "control_name": "Canonical Block Primacy",
            "returns_label": "Reuse blocks/image, blocks/button, blocks/fluid_media",
            "description": "<p>Anywhere a section needs an image, button, video, or other primitive \u2014 use the <strong>canonical</strong> block, not a local one-off. Inline its full settings into the section's <code>blocks</code> array (Fluid's preset expansion requires inline copies, not refs). Standalone <code>blocks/&lt;name&gt;/index.liquid</code> files exist as the source-of-truth specs.</p>",
            "preview_type": "custom",
            "preview_custom_html": "<div class=\"sr-collapsible\">Pattern</div><div class=\"sr-field-label\" style=\"padding:8px;color:#94a3b8;\">See snippets below</div>",
            "schema_label": "Schema",
            "schema_snippet": "&#123;\n  \"blocks\": [\n    &#123; \"type\": \"image\",  \"name\": \"Image\",  \"settings\": [ /* full canonical image schema */ ] &#125;,\n    &#123; \"type\": \"button\", \"name\": \"Button\", \"settings\": [ /* full canonical button schema */ ] &#125;\n  ]\n&#125;",
            "liquid_label": "Liquid",
            "liquid_snippet": "&#123;# Loop matched canonical blocks in section liquid #&#125;\n&#123;% for block in section.blocks %&#125;\n  &#123;% case block.type %&#125;\n    &#123;% when 'image' %&#125;  &#123;% comment %&#125;canonical image markup&#123;% endcomment %&#125;\n    &#123;% when 'button' %&#125; &#123;% comment %&#125;canonical button markup&#123;% endcomment %&#125;\n  &#123;% endcase %&#125;\n&#123;% endfor %&#125;",
            "tip_label": "Exception: data-driven images",
            "tip_kind": "tip",
            "tip": "<p>If the image is bound to a data source (<code>product.images[0].src</code>, <code>post.image_url</code>) \u2014 render directly. Canonical blocks are for editor-uploaded images only.</p>"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "schema_entry",
          "settings": {
            "category": "patterns",
            "anchor_id": "pattern-loop-not-first",
            "is_featured": true,
            "control_name": "Loop, don't `| first`",
            "returns_label": "for + drop limit: 1 \u00b7 enables block duplicate",
            "description": "<p>If you write <code>section.blocks | where: 'type', 'heading' | first</code>, only the first instance of that block ever renders \u2014 even if the editor duplicates it. Symptom: duplicate appears in the editor list but does nothing on the page. Fix: drop <code>limit: 1</code> from the schema and render via a <code>&#123;% for %&#125;</code> loop.</p>",
            "preview_type": "custom",
            "preview_custom_html": "<div class=\"sr-collapsible\">Pattern</div><div class=\"sr-field-label\" style=\"padding:8px;color:#94a3b8;\">See snippets below</div>",
            "schema_label": "Schema",
            "schema_snippet": "&#123; \"type\": \"heading\", \"name\": \"Heading\",\n  \"settings\": [\n    &#123; \"type\": \"richtext\", \"id\": \"text\", \"label\": \"Text\",\n      \"default\": \"<h2>Heading</h2>\" &#125;\n  ] &#125;",
            "liquid_label": "Liquid",
            "liquid_snippet": "&#123;# WRONG \u2014 duplicate doesn't render #&#125;\n&#123;%- assign h = section.blocks | where: 'type', 'heading' | first -%&#125;\n&#123;% if h %&#125;<div &#123;&#123; h.fluid_attributes &#125;&#125;>&#123;&#123; h.settings.text &#125;&#125;</div>&#123;% endif %&#125;\n\n&#123;# RIGHT \u2014 duplicate works #&#125;\n&#123;%- assign hs = section.blocks | where: 'type', 'heading' -%&#125;\n&#123;% for block in hs %&#125;\n  <div &#123;&#123; block.fluid_attributes &#125;&#125;>&#123;&#123; block.settings.text &#125;&#125;</div>\n&#123;% endfor %&#125;",
            "tip_label": "When limit: 1 IS appropriate",
            "tip_kind": "tip",
            "tip": "<p>For blocks with a structurally enforced single slot \u2014 hero image, locale dropdown, primary CTA in a navbar \u2014 keep <code>limit: 1</code>. Editor disables duplicate. Loop over the result anyway so the rendering pattern is consistent.</p>"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "schema_entry",
          "settings": {
            "category": "patterns",
            "anchor_id": "pattern-phantom-default",
            "is_featured": true,
            "control_name": "Phantom Default Antipattern",
            "returns_label": "Wrap in &#123;% if block %&#125; \u00b7 never `| default: \"<p>...\"`",
            "description": "<p>Anti-pattern: <code>&#123;&#123; heading_block.settings.text | default: '&lt;h2&gt;Lorem...&lt;/h2&gt;' &#125;&#125;</code>. When no block of that type is present, the fallback STILL renders \u2014 editors see lorem text on the page they can't click or edit (no block = no fluid_attributes binding). Fix: conditionally render the wrapper.</p>",
            "preview_type": "custom",
            "preview_custom_html": "<div class=\"sr-collapsible\">Pattern</div><div class=\"sr-field-label\" style=\"padding:8px;color:#94a3b8;\">See snippets below</div>",
            "schema_label": "Schema",
            "schema_snippet": "&#123;# Schema: defaults belong on the BLOCK, not on the rendered output #&#125;\n&#123; \"type\": \"heading\", \"name\": \"Heading\",\n  \"settings\": [\n    &#123; \"type\": \"richtext\", \"id\": \"text\", \"label\": \"Text\",\n      \"default\": \"<h2>Default heading</h2>\" &#125;\n  ] &#125;",
            "liquid_label": "Liquid",
            "liquid_snippet": "&#123;# WRONG \u2014 phantom lorem text appears with no editor binding #&#125;\n<div class=\"rte\">&#123;&#123; heading_block.settings.text | default: \"<h2>Lorem...</h2>\" &#125;&#125;</div>\n\n&#123;# RIGHT \u2014 only renders when the block exists #&#125;\n&#123;% if heading_block %&#125;\n  <div class=\"rte\" &#123;&#123; heading_block.fluid_attributes &#125;&#125;>\n    &#123;&#123; heading_block.settings.text &#125;&#125;\n  </div>\n&#123;% endif %&#125;"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "schema_entry",
          "settings": {
            "category": "patterns",
            "anchor_id": "pattern-stat",
            "is_featured": true,
            "control_name": "Stat (Prefix + Value + Suffix + Label)",
            "returns_label": "4 text fields \u00b7 used in stats_bar / hero_split_stats",
            "description": "<p>The atomic unit for any number-driven block: <code>$</code> + <code>49</code> + <code>+</code> + \"Free shipping over\". Three text inputs for the value composition + one for the descriptive label. Stack them in a row or grid.</p>",
            "preview_type": "custom",
            "preview_custom_html": "<div class=\"sr-collapsible\">Pattern</div><div class=\"sr-field-label\" style=\"padding:8px;color:#94a3b8;\">See snippets below</div>",
            "schema_label": "Schema",
            "schema_snippet": "&#123; \"type\": \"stat\", \"name\": \"Stat\",\n  \"settings\": [\n    &#123; \"type\": \"text\", \"id\": \"prefix\", \"label\": \"Prefix\" &#125;,\n    &#123; \"type\": \"text\", \"id\": \"value\",  \"label\": \"Value\",  \"default\": \"10K\" &#125;,\n    &#123; \"type\": \"text\", \"id\": \"suffix\", \"label\": \"Suffix\", \"default\": \"+\" &#125;,\n    &#123; \"type\": \"text\", \"id\": \"label\",  \"label\": \"Label\",  \"default\": \"Happy customers\" &#125;\n  ] &#125;",
            "liquid_label": "Liquid",
            "liquid_snippet": "&#123;% for block in stat_blocks %&#125;\n  <div class=\"stat\" &#123;&#123; block.fluid_attributes &#125;&#125;>\n    <div class=\"stat__value\">\n      &#123;%- if block.settings.prefix != blank -%&#125;&#123;&#123; block.settings.prefix | escape &#125;&#125;&#123;%- endif -%&#125;\n      &#123;&#123; block.settings.value | escape &#125;&#125;\n      &#123;%- if block.settings.suffix != blank -%&#125;&#123;&#123; block.settings.suffix | escape &#125;&#125;&#123;%- endif -%&#125;\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"stat__label\">&#123;&#123; block.settings.label | escape &#125;&#125;</div>\n  </div>\n&#123;% endfor %&#125;"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "schema_entry",
          "settings": {
            "category": "patterns",
            "anchor_id": "pattern-rating-stars",
            "is_featured": true,
            "control_name": "Rating Stars",
            "returns_label": "range 0-5 + SVG loop \u00b7 full + empty colors",
            "description": "<p>0\u20135 star ratings as a <code>range</code>. Render filled stars for the rating, then empty stars to pad to 5. Both colors theme-driven.</p>",
            "preview_type": "custom",
            "preview_custom_html": "<div class=\"sr-collapsible\">Pattern</div><div class=\"sr-field-label\" style=\"padding:8px;color:#94a3b8;\">See snippets below</div>",
            "schema_label": "Schema",
            "schema_snippet": "&#123; \"type\": \"range\", \"id\": \"rating\", \"label\": \"Stars filled\",\n  \"min\": 0, \"max\": 5, \"step\": 1, \"default\": 5 &#125;,\n&#123; \"type\": \"select\", \"id\": \"star_color\",       \"label\": \"Star color\",\n  \"options\": \"background_colors\", \"default\": \"var(--clr-warning)\" &#125;,\n&#123; \"type\": \"select\", \"id\": \"star_empty_color\", \"label\": \"Empty star color\",\n  \"options\": \"background_colors\", \"default\": \"var(--clr-gray)\" &#125;",
            "liquid_label": "Liquid",
            "liquid_snippet": "&#123;%- assign rating = block.settings.rating | default: 5 | plus: 0 -%&#125;\n&#123;%- if rating > 5 -%&#125;&#123;% assign rating = 5 %&#125;&#123;%- endif -%&#125;\n&#123;%- assign empty = 5 | minus: rating -%&#125;\n<div class=\"stars\" style=\"color: &#123;&#123; block.settings.star_color &#125;&#125;;\">\n  &#123;% for i in (1..rating) %&#125;\n    <svg viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\"><polygon points=\"12 2 15.09 8.26 22 9.27 17 14.14 18.18 21.02 12 17.77 5.82 21.02 7 14.14 2 9.27 8.91 8.26 12 2\"/></svg>\n  &#123;% endfor %&#125;\n  &#123;% if empty > 0 %&#125;\n    <span style=\"color: &#123;&#123; block.settings.star_empty_color &#125;&#125;;\">\n      &#123;% for i in (1..empty) %&#125;<svg ...>same star svg</svg>&#123;% endfor %&#125;\n    </span>\n  &#123;% endif %&#125;\n</div>"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "schema_entry",
          "settings": {
            "category": "patterns",
            "anchor_id": "pattern-trust-bar",
            "is_featured": true,
            "control_name": "Trust Bar",
            "returns_label": "Stars + score + count text \u00b7 social proof under hero",
            "description": "<p>Compact trust signal that pairs with hero or product CTAs. Combines the rating-stars pattern with a score number and review count text. One block, three visible elements.</p>",
            "preview_type": "custom",
            "preview_custom_html": "<div class=\"sr-collapsible\">Pattern</div><div class=\"sr-field-label\" style=\"padding:8px;color:#94a3b8;\">See snippets below</div>",
            "schema_label": "Schema",
            "schema_snippet": "&#123; \"type\": \"trust\", \"name\": \"Trust Bar\",\n  \"settings\": [\n    &#123; \"type\": \"checkbox\", \"id\": \"show_stars\", \"label\": \"Show stars\", \"default\": true &#125;,\n    &#123; \"type\": \"range\", \"id\": \"rating\", \"label\": \"Stars filled\",\n      \"min\": 0, \"max\": 5, \"step\": 1, \"default\": 5 &#125;,\n    &#123; \"type\": \"text\", \"id\": \"text\", \"label\": \"Text\",\n      \"default\": \"4.9 from 2,400+ verified reviews\" &#125;\n  ] &#125;",
            "liquid_label": "Liquid",
            "liquid_snippet": "&#123;% for block in trust_blocks %&#125;\n  <div class=\"trust\" &#123;&#123; block.fluid_attributes &#125;&#125;>\n    &#123;% if block.settings.show_stars %&#125;\n      <span class=\"trust__stars\">&#123;% comment %&#125;render stars per rating&#123;% endcomment %&#125;</span>\n    &#123;% endif %&#125;\n    <span>&#123;&#123; block.settings.text | escape &#125;&#125;</span>\n  </div>\n&#123;% endfor %&#125;"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "schema_entry",
          "settings": {
            "category": "patterns",
            "anchor_id": "pattern-tag-pill",
            "is_featured": true,
            "control_name": "Tag Pill",
            "returns_label": "Uppercase label \u00b7 bordered or filled \u00b7 for badges/categories",
            "description": "<p>Small uppercase label with a border or fill, used for categories, status badges, sale flags, etc. Theme-driven background, text, and border colors.</p>",
            "preview_type": "custom",
            "preview_custom_html": "<div class=\"sr-collapsible\">Pattern</div><div class=\"sr-field-label\" style=\"padding:8px;color:#94a3b8;\">See snippets below</div>",
            "schema_label": "Schema",
            "schema_snippet": "&#123; \"type\": \"tag\", \"name\": \"Tag Pill\",\n  \"settings\": [\n    &#123; \"type\": \"text\", \"id\": \"text\", \"label\": \"Text\", \"default\": \"New\" &#125;,\n    &#123; \"type\": \"select\", \"id\": \"background\", \"label\": \"Background\",\n      \"options\": \"background_colors\", \"default\": \"transparent\" &#125;,\n    &#123; \"type\": \"select\", \"id\": \"text_color\", \"label\": \"Text color\",\n      \"options\": \"background_colors\", \"default\": \"var(--clr-primary)\" &#125;,\n    &#123; \"type\": \"select\", \"id\": \"border_color\", \"label\": \"Border color\",\n      \"options\": \"background_colors\", \"default\": \"var(--clr-primary)\" &#125;\n  ] &#125;",
            "liquid_label": "Liquid",
            "liquid_snippet": "&#123;% for block in tag_blocks %&#125;\n  <span class=\"tag\" style=\"background: &#123;&#123; block.settings.background &#125;&#125;; color: &#123;&#123; block.settings.text_color &#125;&#125;; border: 1px solid &#123;&#123; block.settings.border_color &#125;&#125;;\" &#123;&#123; block.fluid_attributes &#125;&#125;>\n    &#123;&#123; block.settings.text | escape &#125;&#125;\n  </span>\n&#123;% endfor %&#125;\n\n<style>\n  .tag &#123;\n    display: inline-flex; align-items: center;\n    padding: 5px 12px;\n    font-size: 11px; font-weight: 600;\n    letter-spacing: 0.06em; text-transform: uppercase;\n    border-radius: 999px;\n  &#125;\n</style>"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "schema_entry",
          "settings": {
            "category": "patterns",
            "anchor_id": "pattern-card-grid",
            "is_featured": true,
            "control_name": "Card Grid (via divider)",
            "returns_label": "CSS grid + divider blocks \u00b7 responsive columns",
            "description": "<p>The composition pattern for any card-driven section: CSS grid wrapper, configurable columns per breakpoint, and divider blocks that group canonical sub-blocks into cards. Used by <code>feature_grid</code>, <code>testimonial_grid</code>, <code>process_steps</code>.</p>",
            "preview_type": "custom",
            "preview_custom_html": "<div class=\"sr-collapsible\">Pattern</div><div class=\"sr-field-label\" style=\"padding:8px;color:#94a3b8;\">See snippets below</div>",
            "schema_label": "Schema",
            "schema_snippet": "&#123;\n  \"settings\": [\n    &#123; \"type\": \"range\", \"id\": \"columns_desktop\", \"label\": \"Columns (desktop)\",\n      \"min\": 1, \"max\": 4, \"step\": 1, \"default\": 3 &#125;,\n    &#123; \"type\": \"range\", \"id\": \"columns_tablet\",  \"label\": \"Columns (tablet)\",\n      \"min\": 1, \"max\": 3, \"step\": 1, \"default\": 2 &#125;,\n    &#123; \"type\": \"range\", \"id\": \"columns_mobile\",  \"label\": \"Columns (mobile)\",\n      \"min\": 1, \"max\": 2, \"step\": 1, \"default\": 1 &#125;,\n    &#123; \"type\": \"range\", \"id\": \"gap\", \"label\": \"Gap (px)\",\n      \"min\": 8, \"max\": 48, \"step\": 2, \"default\": 24 &#125;\n  ]\n&#125;",
            "liquid_label": "Liquid",
            "liquid_snippet": ".grid &#123;\n  display: grid;\n  grid-template-columns: repeat(&#123;&#123; section.settings.columns_desktop &#125;&#125;, minmax(0, 1fr));\n  gap: &#123;&#123; section.settings.gap &#125;&#125;px;\n&#125;\n@media (max-width: 991px) &#123;\n  .grid &#123; grid-template-columns: repeat(&#123;&#123; section.settings.columns_tablet &#125;&#125;, minmax(0, 1fr)); &#125;\n&#125;\n@media (max-width: 767px) &#123;\n  .grid &#123; grid-template-columns: repeat(&#123;&#123; section.settings.columns_mobile &#125;&#125;, minmax(0, 1fr)); gap: 16px; &#125;\n&#125;"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "schema_entry",
          "settings": {
            "category": "patterns",
            "anchor_id": "pattern-css-carousel",
            "is_featured": true,
            "control_name": "CSS Scroll-Snap Carousel",
            "returns_label": "No JS lib \u00b7 scroll-snap track + vanilla arrows/dots",
            "description": "<p>Splide breaks Fluid theme rendering. Use a CSS scroll-snap track + tiny vanilla JS for arrows/dots/autoplay instead. Works for any horizontally-scrolling collection. Used by <code>ugc_carousel</code>.</p>",
            "preview_type": "custom",
            "preview_custom_html": "<div class=\"sr-collapsible\">Pattern</div><div class=\"sr-field-label\" style=\"padding:8px;color:#94a3b8;\">See snippets below</div>",
            "schema_label": "Schema",
            "schema_snippet": "&#123; \"type\": \"range\", \"id\": \"items_desktop\", \"label\": \"Items per view (desktop)\",\n  \"min\": 1, \"max\": 6, \"step\": 1, \"default\": 4 &#125;,\n&#123; \"type\": \"range\", \"id\": \"gap\", \"label\": \"Gap (px)\",\n  \"min\": 0, \"max\": 48, \"step\": 2, \"default\": 16 &#125;,\n&#123; \"type\": \"checkbox\", \"id\": \"loop\",     \"label\": \"Loop\",     \"default\": true &#125;,\n&#123; \"type\": \"checkbox\", \"id\": \"autoplay\", \"label\": \"Autoplay\", \"default\": false &#125;,\n&#123; \"type\": \"checkbox\", \"id\": \"show_arrows\",     \"label\": \"Arrows\", \"default\": true &#125;,\n&#123; \"type\": \"checkbox\", \"id\": \"show_pagination\", \"label\": \"Dots\",   \"default\": false &#125;",
            "liquid_label": "Liquid",
            "liquid_snippet": ".carousel__track &#123;\n  display: grid; grid-auto-flow: column;\n  grid-auto-columns: calc((100% - (&#123;&#123; items_desktop &#125;&#125; - 1) * &#123;&#123; gap &#125;&#125;px) / &#123;&#123; items_desktop &#125;&#125;);\n  gap: &#123;&#123; gap &#125;&#125;px;\n  overflow-x: auto;\n  scroll-snap-type: x mandatory;\n  scroll-behavior: smooth;\n  scrollbar-width: none;\n&#125;\n.carousel__slide &#123; scroll-snap-align: start; &#125;\n\n<script>\n  // arrow.click \u2192 track.scrollTo(&#123; left: track.scrollLeft \u00b1 slideWidth &#125;)\n  // see ugc_carousel for full implementation with loop / autoplay / dots\n</script>",
            "tip_label": "Why no Splide",
            "tip_kind": "tip",
            "tip": "<p>Fluid's editor injects DOM mutations on save. Splide's lifecycle re-mounts on every mutation, double-binds events, and breaks scroll position. Pure CSS scroll-snap is mutation-safe.</p>"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "schema_entry",
          "settings": {
            "category": "patterns",
            "anchor_id": "pattern-native-accordion",
            "is_featured": true,
            "control_name": "Native Accordion",
            "returns_label": "Native <details>/<summary> \u00b7 zero JS \u00b7 fully accessible",
            "description": "<p>For FAQ and any expandable list, use native HTML <code>&lt;details&gt;</code>/<code>&lt;summary&gt;</code>. Zero JS, fully accessible, keyboard navigation built in. Style the marker via <code>::after</code>. Used by <code>faq_accordion</code>.</p>",
            "preview_type": "custom",
            "preview_custom_html": "<div class=\"sr-collapsible\">Pattern</div><div class=\"sr-field-label\" style=\"padding:8px;color:#94a3b8;\">See snippets below</div>",
            "schema_label": "Schema",
            "schema_snippet": "&#123; \"type\": \"faq_item\", \"name\": \"FAQ Item\",\n  \"settings\": [\n    &#123; \"type\": \"text\",     \"id\": \"question\", \"label\": \"Question\" &#125;,\n    &#123; \"type\": \"richtext\", \"id\": \"answer\",   \"label\": \"Answer\" &#125;,\n    &#123; \"type\": \"checkbox\", \"id\": \"open_by_default\", \"label\": \"Open by default\" &#125;\n  ] &#125;",
            "liquid_label": "Liquid",
            "liquid_snippet": "&#123;% for block in faq_items %&#125;\n  <details class=\"faq__item\"&#123;% if block.settings.open_by_default %&#125; open&#123;% endif %&#125; &#123;&#123; block.fluid_attributes &#125;&#125;>\n    <summary>&#123;&#123; block.settings.question | escape &#125;&#125;</summary>\n    <div class=\"faq__answer rte\">&#123;&#123; block.settings.answer &#125;&#125;</div>\n  </details>\n&#123;% endfor %&#125;\n\n<style>\n  .faq__item > summary &#123;\n    list-style: none; cursor: pointer;\n    display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: center;\n  &#125;\n  .faq__item > summary::-webkit-details-marker &#123; display: none; &#125;\n  .faq__item > summary::after &#123;\n    content: \"\";\n    width: 14px; height: 14px;\n    background: currentColor;\n    -webkit-mask: url(\"data:image/svg+xml;...chevron-down\") center / contain no-repeat;\n    transition: transform .2s;\n  &#125;\n  .faq__item[open] > summary::after &#123; transform: rotate(180deg); &#125;\n</style>"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "schema_entry",
          "settings": {
            "category": "patterns",
            "anchor_id": "pattern-drag-slider",
            "is_featured": true,
            "control_name": "Drag Slider (Before/After)",
            "returns_label": "Native input[type=range] overlay + clipped after image",
            "description": "<p>Image-comparison slider with drag handle. Use a transparent native <code>&lt;input type=\"range\"&gt;</code> spanning the full width as the drag affordance \u2014 it gives you free keyboard + touch + accessibility. CSS clips the \"after\" image based on the range value via vanilla JS.</p>",
            "preview_type": "custom",
            "preview_custom_html": "<div class=\"sr-collapsible\">Pattern</div><div class=\"sr-field-label\" style=\"padding:8px;color:#94a3b8;\">See snippets below</div>",
            "schema_label": "Schema",
            "schema_snippet": "&#123; \"type\": \"image_picker\", \"id\": \"before_image\", \"label\": \"Before image\" &#125;,\n&#123; \"type\": \"image_picker\", \"id\": \"after_image\",  \"label\": \"After image\" &#125;,\n&#123; \"type\": \"range\", \"id\": \"initial_position\", \"label\": \"Initial Position\",\n  \"min\": 5, \"max\": 95, \"step\": 5, \"default\": 50, \"unit\": \"%\" &#125;",
            "liquid_label": "Liquid",
            "liquid_snippet": "<div class=\"ba\" data-ba-slider>\n  <img class=\"ba__before\" src=\"&#123;&#123; section.settings.before_image | img_url: '2400x' &#125;&#125;\">\n  <div class=\"ba__after-wrap\" data-ba-after style=\"width: 50%;\">\n    <img src=\"&#123;&#123; section.settings.after_image | img_url: '2400x' &#125;&#125;\">\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"ba__handle\" data-ba-handle></div>\n  <input class=\"ba__range\" type=\"range\" min=\"0\" max=\"100\" value=\"50\" data-ba-range>\n</div>\n\n<script>\n  // range.input \u2192 setPos(v)\n  // setPos: after.style.width = v + '%'; handle.style.left = 'calc(' + v + '% - 22px)';\n  // see before_after section for full implementation\n</script>"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "schema_entry",
          "settings": {
            "category": "patterns",
            "anchor_id": "pattern-cart-button",
            "is_featured": true,
            "control_name": "Cart Button",
            "returns_label": "Icon choices + count badge \u00b7 preserves Fluid JS hooks",
            "description": "<p>Theme-driven cart trigger. 14 settings: icon choice (bag / cart / basket / minimal), style (filled / outline / icon-only), padding, radius, border, all colors theme-driven, count badge with own font-size + colors. Preserves <code>#show-cart</code> + <code>#fluid-cart-count</code> so Fluid's existing cart JS keeps working.</p>",
            "preview_type": "custom",
            "preview_custom_html": "<div class=\"sr-collapsible\">Pattern</div><div class=\"sr-field-label\" style=\"padding:8px;color:#94a3b8;\">See snippets below</div>",
            "schema_label": "Schema",
            "schema_snippet": "&#123; \"type\": \"cart_button\", \"name\": \"Cart Button\", \"limit\": 1,\n  \"settings\": [\n    &#123; \"type\": \"radio\", \"id\": \"icon\", \"label\": \"Icon\", \"default\": \"bag\",\n      \"options\": [\n        &#123; \"value\": \"bag\",     \"label\": \"Shopping Bag\" &#125;,\n        &#123; \"value\": \"cart\",    \"label\": \"Shopping Cart\" &#125;,\n        &#123; \"value\": \"basket\",  \"label\": \"Basket\" &#125;,\n        &#123; \"value\": \"minimal\", \"label\": \"Minimal\" &#125;\n      ] &#125;,\n    &#123; \"type\": \"range\",  \"id\": \"icon_size\", \"min\": 14, \"max\": 32, \"step\": 1, \"default\": 20 &#125;,\n    &#123; \"type\": \"select\", \"id\": \"icon_color\",       \"options\": \"background_colors\", \"default\": \"var(--clr-primary)\" &#125;,\n    &#123; \"type\": \"select\", \"id\": \"count_background\", \"options\": \"background_colors\", \"default\": \"var(--clr-accent)\" &#125;\n    /* + style, padding, border, count_text_color, etc. */\n  ] &#125;",
            "liquid_label": "Liquid",
            "liquid_snippet": "<a href=\"&#123;&#123; cart_url &#125;&#125;\" id=\"show-cart\" class=\"cart-btn\" aria-label=\"Cart\">\n  &#123;% case block.settings.icon %&#125;\n    &#123;% when 'bag' %&#125;<svg>...bag...</svg>\n    &#123;% when 'cart' %&#125;<svg>...cart...</svg>\n    ...\n  &#123;% endcase %&#125;\n  &#123;% if block.settings.show_count %&#125;\n    <span class=\"cart-count\" id=\"fluid-cart-count\">0</span>\n  &#123;% endif %&#125;\n</a>\n\n&#123;# See blocks/cart_button/index.liquid for the full canonical block #&#125;"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "schema_entry",
          "settings": {
            "category": "patterns",
            "anchor_id": "pattern-locale-dropdown",
            "is_featured": true,
            "control_name": "Locale Dropdown",
            "returns_label": "Single component \u00b7 desktop popover + mobile sheet \u00b7 preserves Fluid JS",
            "description": "<p>One unified component renders both the desktop popover and mobile slide-in sheet. Preserves existing Fluid JS hooks (<code>#show-language-country-dropdown</code>, <code>#mobile-country-language</code>, <code>.saveLocaleBtn</code>, <code>.country-selector</code>, <code>.language-selector</code>) so Fluid's built-in locale-switch logic keeps working without touching <code>header.js</code>.</p>",
            "preview_type": "custom",
            "preview_custom_html": "<div class=\"sr-collapsible\">Pattern</div><div class=\"sr-field-label\" style=\"padding:8px;color:#94a3b8;\">See snippets below</div>",
            "schema_label": "Schema",
            "schema_snippet": "&#123; \"type\": \"locale_dropdown\", \"name\": \"Locale Dropdown\", \"limit\": 1,\n  \"settings\": [\n    &#123; \"type\": \"select\", \"id\": \"display_mode\", \"label\": \"Trigger display\", \"default\": \"flag_code\",\n      \"options\": [\n        &#123; \"value\": \"flag_code\", \"label\": \"Flag + code\" &#125;,\n        &#123; \"value\": \"flag_only\", \"label\": \"Flag only\" &#125;,\n        &#123; \"value\": \"code_only\", \"label\": \"Code only\" &#125;,\n        &#123; \"value\": \"flag_name\", \"label\": \"Flag + country name\" &#125;\n      ] &#125;,\n    &#123; \"type\": \"select\", \"id\": \"trigger_color\",   \"options\": \"background_colors\", \"default\": \"var(--clr-body)\" &#125;,\n    &#123; \"type\": \"select\", \"id\": \"panel_background\", \"options\": \"background_colors\", \"default\": \"var(--clr-white)\" &#125;\n    /* + 20+ more theme-driven settings */\n  ] &#125;",
            "liquid_label": "Liquid",
            "liquid_snippet": "&#123;# See components/navbar_locale_dropdown/index.liquid for full markup #&#125;\n&#123;# Trigger uses Fluid globals: current_country_iso, current_country_name, current_selected_locale #&#125;\n&#123;# Panel iterates: countries, language_options #&#125;\n&#123;# Save button: class=\"saveLocaleBtn\" inside class=\"locale-selector\" #&#125;\n\n<button id=\"show-language-country-dropdown\">\n  <span class=\"flag-icon fi fi-&#123;&#123; current_country_iso &#125;&#125;\"></span>\n  &#123;&#123; current_country_iso | upcase &#125;&#125;\n</button>\n\n<div class=\"ld__panel locale-selector\">\n  <select class=\"country-selector\">&#123;% for c in countries %&#125;<option value=\"&#123;&#123; c.iso &#125;&#125;\" &#123;% if c.selected %&#125;selected&#123;% endif %&#125;>&#123;&#123; c.name &#125;&#125;</option>&#123;% endfor %&#125;</select>\n  <select class=\"language-selector\">&#123;% for o in language_options %&#125;<option value=\"&#123;&#123; o.iso &#125;&#125;\" &#123;% if o.selected %&#125;selected&#123;% endif %&#125;>&#123;&#123; o.locale &#125;&#125;</option>&#123;% endfor %&#125;</select>\n  <button class=\"saveLocaleBtn\">Save & close</button>\n</div>"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "schema_entry",
          "settings": {
            "category": "patterns",
            "anchor_id": "pattern-hero-overlay",
            "is_featured": true,
            "control_name": "Hero Overlay (Solid + Gradient)",
            "returns_label": "select color + range opacity + radio style",
            "description": "<p>Heroes need an overlay over the background image to ensure text contrast. Three controls: color (theme-driven), opacity, and style (solid wash vs bottom-up gradient). Renders as a <code>::before</code> pseudo-element to avoid extra DOM.</p>",
            "preview_type": "custom",
            "preview_custom_html": "<div class=\"sr-collapsible\">Pattern</div><div class=\"sr-field-label\" style=\"padding:8px;color:#94a3b8;\">See snippets below</div>",
            "schema_label": "Schema",
            "schema_snippet": "&#123; \"type\": \"select\", \"id\": \"overlay_color\", \"label\": \"Overlay color\",\n  \"options\": \"background_colors\", \"default\": \"var(--clr-dark)\" &#125;,\n&#123; \"type\": \"range\",  \"id\": \"overlay_opacity\", \"label\": \"Overlay opacity\",\n  \"min\": 0, \"max\": 100, \"step\": 5, \"default\": 35, \"unit\": \"%\" &#125;,\n&#123; \"type\": \"radio\",  \"id\": \"overlay_style\", \"label\": \"Overlay style\", \"default\": \"solid\",\n  \"options\": [\n    &#123; \"value\": \"solid\",    \"label\": \"Solid color\" &#125;,\n    &#123; \"value\": \"gradient\", \"label\": \"Bottom gradient (transparent \u2192 color)\" &#125;\n  ] &#125;",
            "liquid_label": "Liquid",
            "liquid_snippet": "&#123;%- if section.settings.overlay_color != blank and section.settings.overlay_opacity > 0 -%&#125;\n  &#123;%- assign _ov = section.settings.overlay_opacity | divided_by: 100.0 -%&#125;\n  .hero::before &#123;\n    content: \"\"; position: absolute; inset: 0;\n    background: &#123;% if section.settings.overlay_style == 'gradient' %&#125;\n      linear-gradient(180deg, transparent 0%, &#123;&#123; section.settings.overlay_color &#125;&#125; 100%)\n    &#123;% else %&#125;\n      &#123;&#123; section.settings.overlay_color &#125;&#125;\n    &#123;% endif %&#125;;\n    opacity: &#123;&#123; _ov &#125;&#125;; pointer-events: none; z-index: 0;\n  &#125;\n&#123;%- endif -%&#125;"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "schema_entry",
          "settings": {
            "category": "patterns",
            "anchor_id": "pattern-scroll-indicator",
            "is_featured": true,
            "control_name": "Scroll Indicator",
            "returns_label": "Animated bouncing arrow at hero bottom",
            "description": "<p>Subtle visual cue at the bottom of full-bleed heroes that says \"there's more below\". Pure CSS keyframe animation, theme-driven color.</p>",
            "preview_type": "custom",
            "preview_custom_html": "<div class=\"sr-collapsible\">Pattern</div><div class=\"sr-field-label\" style=\"padding:8px;color:#94a3b8;\">See snippets below</div>",
            "schema_label": "Schema",
            "schema_snippet": "&#123; \"type\": \"checkbox\", \"id\": \"show_scroll_indicator\", \"label\": \"Show scroll indicator\", \"default\": true &#125;,\n&#123; \"type\": \"text\",     \"id\": \"scroll_label\", \"label\": \"Scroll label\", \"default\": \"Scroll\" &#125;,\n&#123; \"type\": \"select\",   \"id\": \"scroll_color\", \"label\": \"Scroll indicator color\",\n  \"options\": \"background_colors\", \"default\": \"var(--clr-white)\" &#125;",
            "liquid_label": "Liquid",
            "liquid_snippet": "&#123;% if section.settings.show_scroll_indicator %&#125;\n  <div class=\"hero__scroll\">\n    <span>&#123;&#123; section.settings.scroll_label | escape &#125;&#125;</span>\n    <svg viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" stroke=\"currentColor\"><line x1=\"12\" y1=\"5\" x2=\"12\" y2=\"19\"/><polyline points=\"19 12 12 19 5 12\"/></svg>\n  </div>\n&#123;% endif %&#125;\n\n<style>\n  .hero__scroll &#123;\n    position: absolute; bottom: 32px; left: 50%; transform: translateX(-50%);\n    color: &#123;&#123; section.settings.scroll_color &#125;&#125;; opacity: 0.7;\n    display: flex; flex-direction: column; align-items: center; gap: 6px;\n    font-size: 11px; font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: 0.12em; text-transform: uppercase;\n    animation: scrollBounce 2.4s infinite ease-in-out;\n  &#125;\n  @keyframes scrollBounce &#123;\n    0%, 100% &#123; transform: translate(-50%, 0); &#125;\n    50%      &#123; transform: translate(-50%, 6px); &#125;\n  &#125;\n</style>"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "schema_entry",
          "settings": {
            "category": "patterns",
            "anchor_id": "pattern-comparison-row",
            "is_featured": true,
            "control_name": "Comparison Row (Check / X / Text)",
            "returns_label": "radio with 3 visual modes \u00b7 for us-vs-them tables",
            "description": "<p>Each row in a comparison table picks how it displays for each column: a checkmark (yes), an X (no), or free text. Used by <code>comparison_table</code>. The radio control switches markup, not just styling.</p>",
            "preview_type": "custom",
            "preview_custom_html": "<div class=\"sr-collapsible\">Pattern</div><div class=\"sr-field-label\" style=\"padding:8px;color:#94a3b8;\">See snippets below</div>",
            "schema_label": "Schema",
            "schema_snippet": "&#123; \"type\": \"row\", \"name\": \"Row\",\n  \"settings\": [\n    &#123; \"type\": \"text\", \"id\": \"feature\", \"label\": \"Feature\", \"default\": \"Free shipping\" &#125;,\n    &#123; \"type\": \"radio\", \"id\": \"us_value\", \"label\": \"Our column\", \"default\": \"check\",\n      \"options\": [\n        &#123; \"value\": \"check\", \"label\": \"Checkmark\" &#125;,\n        &#123; \"value\": \"x\",     \"label\": \"Cross\" &#125;,\n        &#123; \"value\": \"text\",  \"label\": \"Text\" &#125;\n      ] &#125;,\n    &#123; \"type\": \"text\", \"id\": \"us_text\", \"label\": \"Text (if Display = Text)\", \"default\": \"Yes\" &#125;\n    /* + them_value, them_text */\n  ] &#125;",
            "liquid_label": "Liquid",
            "liquid_snippet": "&#123;% case block.settings.us_value %&#125;\n  &#123;% when 'check' %&#125;\n    <svg class=\"check\"><polyline points=\"20 6 9 17 4 12\"/></svg>\n  &#123;% when 'x' %&#125;\n    <svg class=\"x\"><line x1=\"18\" y1=\"6\" x2=\"6\" y2=\"18\"/><line x1=\"6\" y1=\"6\" x2=\"18\" y2=\"18\"/></svg>\n  &#123;% else %&#125;\n    <span>&#123;&#123; block.settings.us_text | escape &#125;&#125;</span>\n&#123;% endcase %&#125;"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "schema_entry",
          "settings": {
            "category": "patterns",
            "anchor_id": "pattern-connector-line",
            "is_featured": true,
            "control_name": "Connector Line (Timeline)",
            "returns_label": "CSS pseudo-element on .step:not(:last-child)",
            "description": "<p>For process-step / timeline UIs. A single CSS pseudo-element on each step (except the last) draws the connecting line. No extra DOM. Vertical or horizontal, theme-driven color, hidden on mobile.</p>",
            "preview_type": "custom",
            "preview_custom_html": "<div class=\"sr-collapsible\">Pattern</div><div class=\"sr-field-label\" style=\"padding:8px;color:#94a3b8;\">See snippets below</div>",
            "schema_label": "Schema",
            "schema_snippet": "&#123; \"type\": \"checkbox\", \"id\": \"show_connector\", \"label\": \"Show connecting line\", \"default\": true &#125;,\n&#123; \"type\": \"select\",   \"id\": \"connector_color\", \"label\": \"Connector color\",\n  \"options\": \"background_colors\", \"default\": \"var(--clr-gray)\" &#125;",
            "liquid_label": "Liquid",
            "liquid_snippet": "&#123;# Horizontal #&#125;\n&#123;%- if section.settings.show_connector -%&#125;\n  .step:not(:last-child)::after &#123;\n    content: \"\";\n    position: absolute;\n    top: 28px;  /* center of number circle */\n    left: calc(50% + 36px);\n    right: calc(-50% + 36px);\n    height: 2px;\n    background: &#123;&#123; section.settings.connector_color &#125;&#125;;\n    z-index: 1;\n  &#125;\n  @media (max-width: 767px) &#123; .step:not(:last-child)::after &#123; display: none; &#125; &#125;\n&#123;%- endif -%&#125;"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "schema_entry",
          "settings": {
            "category": "patterns",
            "anchor_id": "pattern-glass-morphism",
            "is_featured": true,
            "control_name": "Glass Morphism (Backdrop Blur)",
            "returns_label": "backdrop-filter pill \u00b7 for badges over images",
            "description": "<p>For floating badges, captions, or controls layered over images: semi-transparent background + <code>backdrop-filter: blur()</code> creates a frosted-glass effect. Use sparingly \u2014 great for one or two elements per page, distracting if overused.</p>",
            "preview_type": "custom",
            "preview_custom_html": "<div class=\"sr-collapsible\">Pattern</div><div class=\"sr-field-label\" style=\"padding:8px;color:#94a3b8;\">See snippets below</div>",
            "schema_label": "Schema",
            "schema_snippet": "&#123; \"type\": \"select\", \"id\": \"glass_background\", \"label\": \"Background\",\n  \"options\": \"background_colors\", \"default\": \"var(--clr-white)\" &#125;,\n&#123; \"type\": \"range\",  \"id\": \"glass_opacity\", \"label\": \"Opacity\",\n  \"min\": 0, \"max\": 100, \"step\": 5, \"default\": 90, \"unit\": \"%\" &#125;",
            "liquid_label": "Liquid",
            "liquid_snippet": ".glass-pill &#123;\n  display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 6px;\n  padding: 6px 14px;\n  background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.15);\n  color: var(--clr-white);\n  border-radius: 999px;\n  font-size: 12px; font-weight: 600; text-transform: uppercase;\n  backdrop-filter: blur(8px);\n  -webkit-backdrop-filter: blur(8px);\n&#125;",
            "tip_label": "Don't blur over solid backgrounds",
            "tip_kind": "tip",
            "tip": "<p>backdrop-filter has no visible effect over solid colors \u2014 it only blurs whatever's behind it. Reserve it for elements that float over images or video.</p>"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "schema_entry",
          "settings": {
            "category": "patterns",
            "anchor_id": "pattern-editorial-meta-column",
            "is_featured": true,
            "control_name": "Editorial Meta Column",
            "returns_label": "writing-mode: vertical-rl \u00b7 sidebar of meta labels",
            "description": "<p>Magazine-style sidebar of small meta labels (\"Issue 04\", \"Spring 2026\") rotated vertically beside the main content. Single CSS property turns horizontal text into vertical text \u2014 no DOM hacks. Used by <code>hero_editorial</code>.</p>",
            "preview_type": "custom",
            "preview_custom_html": "<div class=\"sr-collapsible\">Pattern</div><div class=\"sr-field-label\" style=\"padding:8px;color:#94a3b8;\">See snippets below</div>",
            "schema_label": "Schema",
            "schema_snippet": "&#123; \"type\": \"meta\", \"name\": \"Meta Label\",\n  \"settings\": [\n    &#123; \"type\": \"text\", \"id\": \"text\", \"label\": \"Text\", \"default\": \"Issue 04\" &#125;\n  ] &#125;",
            "liquid_label": "Liquid",
            "liquid_snippet": "<aside class=\"meta-col\">\n  &#123;% for block in meta_blocks %&#125;\n    <span class=\"meta-label\" &#123;&#123; block.fluid_attributes &#125;&#125;>&#123;&#123; block.settings.text | escape &#125;&#125;</span>\n  &#123;% endfor %&#125;\n</aside>\n\n<style>\n  @media (min-width: 992px) &#123;\n    .meta-col &#123;\n      writing-mode: vertical-rl;\n      transform: rotate(180deg);\n      display: flex; gap: 24px;\n    &#125;\n  &#125;\n  .meta-label &#123;\n    font-size: 11px; font-weight: 600;\n    letter-spacing: 0.18em; text-transform: uppercase;\n    color: var(--clr-muted);\n  &#125;\n</style>"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "schema_entry",
          "settings": {
            "category": "patterns",
            "anchor_id": "pattern-image-stretch-override",
            "is_featured": true,
            "control_name": "Image Stretch Override",
            "returns_label": "When canonical image fills a hero column, override aspect-ratio",
            "description": "<p>The canonical image block has its own <code>aspect_ratio</code> control \u2014 great when the image is sized by ratio. But when the image needs to FILL a parent column (like in a 50/50 hero), the section CSS must override the ratio and let the image stretch.</p>",
            "preview_type": "custom",
            "preview_custom_html": "<div class=\"sr-collapsible\">Pattern</div><div class=\"sr-field-label\" style=\"padding:8px;color:#94a3b8;\">See snippets below</div>",
            "schema_label": "Schema",
            "schema_snippet": "&#123;# In hero_split_stats schema, the image block keeps its full canonical settings.\n   The section's CSS overrides ratio/sizing instead. #&#125;\n\n&#123; \"type\": \"image\", \"name\": \"Hero Image\", \"limit\": 1,\n  \"settings\": [ /* full canonical image settings */ ] &#125;",
            "liquid_label": "Liquid",
            "liquid_snippet": "/* In the hero section's CSS, override the image block's wrapper */\n.hero__image-slot &#123; align-self: stretch; position: relative; min-height: 360px; &#125;\n\n.hero__image-slot .media-wrap &#123;\n  position: absolute; inset: 0;\n  width: 100%; height: 100%;\n  aspect-ratio: unset !important;  /* override canonical block's setting */\n  margin: 0 !important;\n&#125;\n.hero__image-slot .media-wrap img &#123;\n  width: 100%; height: 100%; object-fit: cover;\n&#125;"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "schema_entry",
          "settings": {
            "category": "patterns",
            "anchor_id": "pattern-media-picker-fallback",
            "is_featured": true,
            "control_name": "Media Picker Fallback",
            "returns_label": "Handle Fluid media + plain image upload",
            "description": "<p>The <code>media_picker</code> control returns two different shapes depending on what the editor picked: a Fluid Media object with <code>fluid_media_id</code> (when picking a Fluid video / UGC asset) OR a plain image object (when uploading a JPG/PNG). Always handle both \u2014 fall through to <code>| image_url</code> when no media id is present.</p>",
            "preview_type": "custom",
            "preview_custom_html": "<div class=\"sr-collapsible\">Pattern</div><div class=\"sr-field-label\" style=\"padding:8px;color:#94a3b8;\">See snippets below</div>",
            "schema_label": "Schema",
            "schema_snippet": "&#123; \"type\": \"media_picker\", \"id\": \"media\", \"label\": \"Media\" &#125;",
            "liquid_label": "Liquid",
            "liquid_snippet": "&#123;%- assign _m = block.settings.media -%&#125;\n&#123;%- assign _fmid = _m.fluid_media_id -%&#125;\n&#123;%- assign _img_url = '' -%&#125;\n&#123;%- if _fmid == blank and _m -%&#125;\n  &#123;%- assign _img_url = _m | image_url -%&#125;\n  &#123;%- if _img_url == blank -%&#125;&#123;%- assign _img_url = _m.src | default: _m.url -%&#125;&#123;%- endif -%&#125;\n&#123;%- endif -%&#125;\n\n&#123;% if _fmid != blank %&#125;\n  <fluid-media-widget media-id=\"&#123;&#123; _fmid &#125;&#125;\" embed-type=\"&#123;&#123; _embed &#125;&#125;\" responsive=\"true\" data-fluid-widget=\"true\"></fluid-media-widget>\n&#123;% elsif _img_url != blank %&#125;\n  <img src=\"&#123;&#123; _img_url &#125;&#125;\" alt=\"\" loading=\"lazy\">\n&#123;% else %&#125;\n  <div class=\"media-wrap__placeholder\">\u2026</div>\n&#123;% endif %&#125;"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "schema_entry",
          "settings": {
            "category": "patterns",
            "anchor_id": "pattern-product-image-fallback",
            "is_featured": true,
            "control_name": "Product Image Fallback Chain",
            "returns_label": "product.images[0].src \u2192 product.image_url \u2192 product.image | image_url",
            "description": "<p>Fluid product objects carry images in different shapes depending on context. Always check the chain in order: <code>product.images[0].src</code> (most explicit), then <code>product.image_url</code>, then <code>product.image | image_url</code>. Render a placeholder if all fail.</p>",
            "preview_type": "custom",
            "preview_custom_html": "<div class=\"sr-collapsible\">Pattern</div><div class=\"sr-field-label\" style=\"padding:8px;color:#94a3b8;\">See snippets below</div>",
            "schema_label": "Schema",
            "schema_snippet": "&#123;# No schema \u2014 reads from Fluid's product object #&#125;",
            "liquid_label": "Liquid",
            "liquid_snippet": "&#123;%- assign _pimg_url = '' -%&#125;\n&#123;%- if product.images and product.images.size > 0 -%&#125;\n  &#123;%- assign _pimg_url = product.images[0].src -%&#125;\n&#123;%- elsif product.image_url != blank -%&#125;\n  &#123;%- assign _pimg_url = product.image_url -%&#125;\n&#123;%- elsif product.image -%&#125;\n  &#123;%- assign _pimg_url = product.image | image_url -%&#125;\n&#123;%- endif -%&#125;\n\n&#123;% if _pimg_url != blank %&#125;\n  <img src=\"&#123;&#123; _pimg_url &#125;&#125;\" alt=\"&#123;&#123; product.title | escape &#125;&#125;\" loading=\"lazy\">\n&#123;% else %&#125;\n  <div class=\"media-wrap__placeholder\">\u2026</div>\n&#123;% endif %&#125;"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "schema_entry",
          "settings": {
            "category": "patterns",
            "anchor_id": "pattern-collection-fallback",
            "is_featured": true,
            "control_name": "Collection Fallback Chain",
            "returns_label": "collection.image_url \u2192 first product.image_url",
            "description": "<p>For collection tiles / category cards: a collection's own <code>image_url</code> is often null (not all stores set it). Fall back to the first product's image so every tile renders something.</p>",
            "preview_type": "custom",
            "preview_custom_html": "<div class=\"sr-collapsible\">Pattern</div><div class=\"sr-field-label\" style=\"padding:8px;color:#94a3b8;\">See snippets below</div>",
            "schema_label": "Schema",
            "schema_snippet": "&#123; \"type\": \"collection\", \"id\": \"collection\", \"label\": \"Collection\" &#125;",
            "liquid_label": "Liquid",
            "liquid_snippet": "&#123;%- assign _col = block.settings.collection -%&#125;\n&#123;%- assign _img_url = '' -%&#125;\n&#123;%- if _col.image_url != blank -%&#125;\n  &#123;%- assign _img_url = _col.image_url -%&#125;\n&#123;%- elsif _col.image_path != blank -%&#125;\n  &#123;%- assign _img_url = _col.image_path -%&#125;\n&#123;%- elsif _col.product_collections -%&#125;\n  &#123;%- for pc in _col.product_collections limit: 1 -%&#125;\n    &#123;%- if pc.product.image_url != blank -%&#125;&#123;%- assign _img_url = pc.product.image_url -%&#125;&#123;%- endif -%&#125;\n  &#123;%- endfor -%&#125;\n&#123;%- elsif _col.products -%&#125;\n  &#123;%- for p in _col.products limit: 1 -%&#125;\n    &#123;%- if p.image_url != blank -%&#125;&#123;%- assign _img_url = p.image_url -%&#125;&#123;%- endif -%&#125;\n  &#123;%- endfor -%&#125;\n&#123;%- endif -%&#125;\n\n&#123;# Also check canonical_url for the collection link, NOT .url #&#125;\n&#123;%- assign _href = _col.canonical_url | default: _col.url | default: '#' -%&#125;"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "schema_entry",
          "settings": {
            "category": "patterns",
            "anchor_id": "pattern-preset-expansion",
            "is_featured": true,
            "control_name": "Preset Expansion Workflow",
            "returns_label": "Destroy template + re-push to refresh blocks",
            "description": "<p>Section presets only expand on <em>fresh template creation</em> \u2014 not on resource updates. After changing a section's block structure (adding new block types, removing old ones), the existing template instance still has the old blocks. To refresh: destroy the template via API, then re-push the page template file. Fluid creates a new template record and runs preset expansion.</p>",
            "preview_type": "custom",
            "preview_custom_html": "<div class=\"sr-collapsible\">Pattern</div><div class=\"sr-field-label\" style=\"padding:8px;color:#94a3b8;\">See snippets below</div>",
            "schema_label": "Schema",
            "schema_snippet": "&#123;# No schema \u2014 it's an API workflow #&#125;",
            "liquid_label": "Liquid",
            "liquid_snippet": "# 1. Find the template's resource_id\ncurl -H \"Authorization: Bearer $TOKEN\" \\\n  \"https://$COMPANY.fluid.app/api/application_themes/$THEME_ID/resources\" \\\n  | jq '.application_theme_resources[] | select(.key == \"home_page/default/index.liquid\")'\n\n# 2. Destroy the template (this clears the old block instances)\ncurl -X DELETE -H \"Authorization: Bearer $TOKEN\" \\\n  \"https://$COMPANY.fluid.app/api/application_theme_templates/$TEMPLATE_ID\"\n# \u2192 \"Template was successfully destroyed.\"\n\n# 3. Re-push the template file\ncurl -X PUT -H \"Authorization: Bearer $TOKEN\" \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -d '&#123;\"key\":\"home_page/default/index.liquid\",\"content\":\"...\"&#125;' \\\n  \"https://$COMPANY.fluid.app/api/application_themes/$THEME_ID/resources\"\n# \u2192 fresh template with preset blocks expanded",
            "tip_label": "DELETE /resources alone is not enough",
            "tip_kind": "tip",
            "tip": "<p>The <code>DELETE /api/application_themes/{id}/resources</code> endpoint with a key in the body returns 200 but only nulls the content \u2014 the underlying <code>ApplicationThemeTemplate</code> record persists. To fully destroy a template (so re-push triggers fresh preset expansion), use <code>DELETE /api/application_theme_templates/{template_id}</code>.</p>"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "schema_entry",
          "settings": {
            "category": "patterns",
            "anchor_id": "pattern-liquid-comments",
            "is_featured": true,
            "control_name": "Liquid Comments",
            "returns_label": "&#123;% comment %&#125; not &#123;# #&#125;",
            "description": "<p>Fluid uses <strong>Liquid</strong>, not Jinja or Twig. Jinja-style <code>&#123;# comment #&#125;</code> tags render as literal text on the page \u2014 the parser doesn't recognize them. Always use <code>&#123;% comment %&#125;</code> / <code>&#123;% endcomment %&#125;</code>.</p>",
            "preview_type": "custom",
            "preview_custom_html": "<div class=\"sr-collapsible\">Pattern</div><div class=\"sr-field-label\" style=\"padding:8px;color:#94a3b8;\">See snippets below</div>",
            "schema_label": "Schema",
            "schema_snippet": "&#123;# No schema \u2014 syntax rule #&#125;",
